.TH MU2EDAQ\-DISK\-WRITER 1 "June 2026" "mu2edaq-downtime-logger 0.1.0" "Mu2e DAQ Tools"
.SH NAME
mu2edaq\-disk\-writer \- disk-activity diagnostic for DiskActivityDetector
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B python \-m tools.disk_writer
\fB\-\-path\fR \fIDIR\fR
[\fB\-\-interval\fR \fISECS\fR]
[\fB\-\-filename\fR \fINAME\fR]
[\fB\-\-once\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B disk_writer
periodically creates and updates a file inside a watched directory so that
.B DiskActivityDetector
sees fresh filesystem modifications and reports the DAQ as UP.
.PP
The target directory is created if it does not exist. The tool appends the
current Unix timestamp to the file on each write and also calls
\fButime\fR(2) to update the modification time, satisfying detectors that
check either file content or mtime.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-path\fR \fIDIR\fR
Directory to write into. Created automatically if absent. Required.
.TP
\fB\-\-interval\fR \fISECS\fR
Seconds between writes. Default: \fB5.0\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-filename\fR \fINAME\fR
Filename to create inside \fIDIR\fR. Default: \fB.heartbeat\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-once
Write once and exit instead of looping.
.SH EXAMPLES
Keep \fI/data/raw\fR active every 5 seconds:
.PP
.RS
.nf
python \-m tools.disk_writer \-\-path /data/raw \-\-interval 5
.fi
.RE
.PP
Write once to \fI/tmp/daq\-test\fR:
.PP
.RS
.nf
python \-m tools.disk_writer \-\-path /tmp/daq\-test \-\-once
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mu2edaq\-log\-writer (1),
.BR mu2edaq\-downtime\-logger (1)
